            "config": {
              "id": "QUE62915",
              "question": "You are waiting at the airport for your flight to arrive. You and the others at your gate are not a group. Why not?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "You do not have cultural backgrounds in common."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "You are likely to get annoyed with each other’s behavior."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "You will maintain long-term relationships."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "You are a loosely formed collection of people with very little interaction."
                }
              ]
            },
            "answerKey": {
              "assessmentType": "multiplechoice",
              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Groups can have long- and short-term existences. \n\u003cem\u003eLO 5.1 \u003c/em\u003eDiscuss the main characteristics of primary groups, secondary groups, ingroups and out-groups, reference groups, and social networks."
                },
                "answer_2": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Group membership does not guarantee you will always get along with or disagree with other group members. LO 5.1 Discuss the main characteristics of primary groups, secondary groups, ingroups and out-groups, reference groups, and social networks."
                },
                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Groups can be organized based on many criteria, but it does not have to be cultural backgrounds. LO 5.1 Discuss the main characteristics of primary groups, secondary groups, ingroups and out-groups, reference groups, and social networks."
                },
                "answer_4": {
                  "score": 1.0,
                  "response": "That’s correct!"
                }
              }
            },
